This paper deals with multi-agent modal logic, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses different semantics for modeling ambiguity, which is related to the study of logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper examines the expressive power of logics, which is a topic in mathematical logic (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the interpretation of information by different agents, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of ambiguity for security and cryptography, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR).
